<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/c7db737be14f778b0897d6f21eb5a737.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 8 and c = 13. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>10.2</li><li>38.0</li><li>52.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{13}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{169}={64}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{169}-{64}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{105}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{105}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{10.24695076596}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{10.2}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{13}}\right)}}}\approx{37.97987244488}\approx{38}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{13}}\right)}}}\approx{52.02012755512}\approx{52}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

